Hello! Here's what I learned:
1. Always use scissors on a 'soft' item, never 'hard'.
2. The highest score (100) comes from combining a 'cut artificial' item with a 'cut natural' item, then framing the result.
3. Combining two cut items (even if both artificial or both natural) and then framing them usually yields a 70-75 score.
4. Framing any combined item significantly boosts its value. Don't frame two separate items and then combine them.
Good luck!

Then, use the 'frame' tool on the resulting 'cut' item. This 'framed cut [natural, soft]' item will be your highest value. Do NOT combine the 'framed cut' item with any 'cut artificial' item, as it ruins the frame and drops the value. Combining raw ingredients (like hard + hard or hard + soft) yields items worth around 30, which is lower than 45. Your best bet is to make the framed cut natural item and submit.

message: To reach 100 points, always aim for: 1. Use 'scissors' on a 'natural, soft' item (e.g., flower) to create a 'cut, natural' item. 2. Use 'scissors' on an 'artificial, soft' item (e.g., ribbon) to create a 'cut, artificial' item. 3. Combine the 'cut, natural' and 'cut, artificial' items (this yields 80 points). 4. Use 'frame' on this combined item (this yields 100 points). If you only have 'hard' items, combine 'natural, hard' + 'artificial, hard' (30 points), then 'frame' it (50 points). Avoid combining two 'natural, hard' items (0 points) and combining more than two items, especially if one is already framed (can lead to very negative values).
